# unlink() – Delete a File

`unlink(string $filename): bool` deletes a file. Returns true on success, false on failure (e.g., no permission).

```php
if (unlink('oldfile.txt')) {
    echo "File deleted.";
} else {
    echo "Failed to delete.";
}
```

⚠️ Files are permanently deleted, not sent to trash.

```php
<?php
$file = 'temp.txt';
if (file_exists($file)) {
    if (unlink($file)) {
        echo "$file deleted.";
    } else {
        echo "Could not delete $file.";
    }
} else {
    echo "$file does not exist.";
}
?>
```

